iving events and argues that blood donation has become a site not only of frenetic competition between different devotional movements, but also of intense spiritual creativity. Despite tensions between blood banks and these religious groups, their collaboration is a remarkable success storyùthe nation's blood supply is replenished while blood donors discover new devotional possibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBlood donorsxIndiaxDelhi. 0aBlood donorszIndiazDelhi. 0aBloodxCollection and preservationxIndiaxDelhi. 0aBloodxCollection and preservationzIndiazDelhi. 0aBloodxReligious aspects. 0aBloodxSocial aspectsxIndiaxDelhi. 0aBloodxSocial aspectszIndiazDelhi. 0aKinshipxIndiaxDelhi. 0aKinshipzIndiazDelhi. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081354596740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813545967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813545967/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK